\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Singular-value spectra of attention ($W_Q,W_K,W_V$ concatenated, blue) versus FFN (gate, up, down concatenated, orange) for five layers of Llama-3.1-8B. Attention curves drop ${\sim }3$ orders of magnitude inside the first 1\,500 components; FFN curves stay within one order of magnitude across the full $d{=}4096$ axis. This is the geometric premise that justifies compressing attention exclusively (Fig.~\ref {fig:spectra-app} shows the same effect averaged across all 32 layers).}}{31}{figure.caption.32}\protected@file@percent }
